---
import ChevronLeft from "@icons/ChevronLeft.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import P from "@components/P.astro";
---

<Layout title="Shlok Desai | Executive Board Member @ JYI">
  <div class="flex justify-center max-w-7xl gap-x-16 mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="w-40 hidden xl:block">
      <button
        onclick="history.back();"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-1 border-b border-gray9
              hover:border-gray11 hover:text-gray12 transition-colors w-fit
              tracking-wide font-light text-gray12 text-base"
      >
        <ChevronLeft size={16} />
         cd . .
      </button>
    </div>

    <div id="main" class="max-w-2xl w-full">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h1 class="text-gray12 tracking-wider">
          Executive Board Member{" "}
          <span class="text-gray11 font-light">@ JYI</span>
        </h1>

        <button
          onclick="history.back();"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-1 border-b border-gray9
              hover:border-gray11 hover:text-gray12 transition-colors w-fit
              tracking-wide font-light text-gray12 text-base xl:hidden"
        >
          <ChevronLeft size={16} />
           cd . .
        </button>
      </div>

      <span class="text-gray11 font-light text-sm mt-4 block">
        Remote â€¢ 04/2023 - Present
      </span>

      <P className="mt-8">
        As the first peer-reviewed undergraduate journal dedicated to
        international science scholarship, The Journal of Young Investigators
        engages students in research, publishing, and creative science
        communication while fostering a culture of personal and professional
        development. JYI draws its staff from around the world and maintains a
        network of experienced mentors who provide in-depth advice throughout
        the scientific writing and reviewing processes
      </P>

      <P className="mt-4">
        As Chief Technology Officer, I am responsible for the technological
        direction and resources of the Journal of Young Investigators. This
        includes overseeing and executing JYI's short and long-term technical
        goals, and the management of department staff and organizational
        technology needs. I also meet regularly with the Executive Board to
        demonstrate progress and vote on organizational decisions, provide
        regular reports to Executive Board and Board of Directors, and maintain
        my position handbook and other resources.
      </P>

      <P className="mt-8">Responsibilites:</P>

      <ul class="mt-4 list-disc text-gray11">
        <li>
          <P>
            Leading the technology department of JYI, providing a vision for its
            future and establishing, planning, and executing requisite goals.
          </P>
        </li>
        <li>
          <P>
            Maintaining and updating JYI's website, web applications, staff
            tools, and other technology resources.
          </P>
        </li>
        <li>
          <P>
            Managing JYI's technology department which includes Software
            Engineers, Development Officers, and others.
          </P>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="pt-4"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-40 hidden xl:block"></div>
  </div>
</Layout>
